headline: Does S&P Global’s Recent Headlines Signal Room for Growth in 2025?
summary: Thinking about what to do with S&P Global stock? You are not alone. Plenty of investors are eyeing its price movements and asking if there is still value left in one of the world's leading data providers. Over the past week, S&P Global’s share price has edged up 2.0%, capping off a modest 1.3% gain over the past month. While those numbers are not jaw-dropping, what stands out is the stock's resilient longer-term gains: 60.1% over three years and 53.7% over five years. Even as 2024 has seen a...
